# Mulesoft Common Project
The MuleSoft Common Project is a centralized repository that contains reusable MuleSoft APIs, shared connectors, utility modules, templates, and core integration components used across multiple business domains and application projects.
The purpose of this project is to promote consistency, reduce code duplication, enforce standards, and accelerate the development of integration solutions in a scalable and maintainable way.
This repository should serve as the source of truth for reusable integration logic that adheres to the organization’s API-Led Connectivity principles.